The paper discusses testing stateful abstractions and the use of mocking frameworks, which are common topics in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The study focuses on metrics such as code size and cyclomatic complexity, which are often used in machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper argues for a more stylistically appropriate approach to testing in the Scala community, which could fall under the category of other computer science (cs.OH).
